description: Test the diode in the load module to ensure it is not open or shorted, and verify that it is allowing current to pass in the correct direction now that polarity is correct., outcome='The enclosure was successfully inverted to access internal components. The load protection diode is functioning nominally, with a forward voltage of 0.7 V matching the expected value. No issues with diode polarity or performance were detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_diode', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Lamp and Lamp Indicator (bulbs) in Load Module,
description: Test both the main lamp and the internal indicator lamp in the load module to check for continuity and confirm if either or both bulbs are functional or have failed (open circuit)., outcome='Both the main lamp and the internal indicator lamp show nominal continuity with resistance values matching their nominal specifications (120 Ω and 500 Ω, respectively). This confirms that both bulbs are functional and have not failed (not open circuit).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=50.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load Module Connections,
description: Test for the presence of 12V supply and ground at the input terminals of the load module to verify that voltage is actually reaching the load module when the switch is closed., outcome='No voltage is present at either the Load Input Cable (+) or Load Input Cable (−) terminals; both measure 0.0 V with respect to ground. This indicates that 12V supply is not reaching the load module input terminals during this test.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module Output Connections,
description: Test the voltage at the output terminals of the control module when the switch is closed, to verify if 12V and ground are being supplied out of the control module towards the load module., outcome="Voltage measurements at both 'Control Output Cable (+)' and 'Control Output Cable (−)' are 0.0 V. No voltage is being supplied out of the control module towards the load module when the switch is closed.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Internal wiring and continuity inside the Control Module,
description: Test the internal wiring continuity from the Control Module input terminals (where PSU output is connected) to the points after the switch and the output terminals. Check if there is an internal wiring break or connection fault preventing voltage from reaching the output., outcome='The path from Control Input Cable (+) to the Control Switch is continuous (short), but there is an open circuit from the Control Switch to the Control Output Cable (+), indicating a wiring break or disconnection on this path. The path from Control Input Cable (−) through the LED and resistor to Control Output Cable (−) is continuous (low resistances), so there is no break on the negative path. No polarity inversion is detected in the tested paths.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=160.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
